         <abstract>The
		  Junaluska School of Religion was a summer program sponsored
		  by the Duke School of Religion at Lake Junaluska, N.C. From
		  the late 1920s to early 1940s, Methodist scholars and
		  leaders attended the summer school. The collection mainly
		  consists of correspondence, as well as reports,
		  recommendations, registration cards, and other materials.
		  Major subjects include the school's administration, student
		  enrollment, curriculum, and planning. 
            English.
         </abstract>
         
