      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         
         
         <head>Historical Note</head>
         
         
         <p>From the late 1928 to the about 1941, the Duke
		  School of Religion sponsored a summer school program at
		  Lake Junaluska in western North Carolina. Called the
		  Junaluska School of Religion, the program allowed Methodist
		  leaders and scholars to gather and take college-level
		  courses in theology. Due to a decline in enrollment and
		  teachers, the program was discontinued in the early
		  1940s.</p>
      
      
      </bioghist>
      
      
      <scopecontent>
         
         
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         
         
         <p>The collection mainly includes correspondence, as
		  well as reports, recommendations, registration cards, and
		  other materials. Major topics include the administration of
		  the school, student enrollment, curriculum, and
		  planning.</p>
      
      
      </scopecontent>
      
      
